{
  "stem": "13096.1",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "The few more shops, they were from Greeks or other ones, it was not worth visiting.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Like Italian people and Turkish people and Greek people who live in the island never came into the Jewish quarter to shop because there was no-- no point.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "It was all the shops were closed.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah, at the certain point, when the prosperity, you know, they were prospering in the community, they had 5,000 Jews.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But after, you know, they started having, you know, the martial laws and this and that.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So people, they were not feeling secure any more in Rhodes Island, and they tried to immigrate.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "People went to South America, to Africa, and even to Palestine.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My address was 16 Via Heredia, H-E-R-E-D-I-A, which it was named after Grand Maestro, which it was a Cavalier.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because Rhodes Island was occupied of the century sometimes by the Turkish, by the Ottoman Empire, for sometimes by the Arabs.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But and at one time the most, you know, the Cavaliers, that they were like the knights, you know, the Knights of St.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "John's.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They were occupying Rhodes Island and then many, many streets were named after their names.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So Via Heredia was the name of one the big Cavaliers or whatever you call it.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, it was-- you know, in Rhodes Island, there were schools for Jewish people, schools for Greeks, schools for Turkish, and schools for Italians.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So each one, you know, attend to his own school.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So ourselves, we went to the Jewish school and then it was, you know, the-- the fashion when you finish the school, which it was standards in high school, like three or four high school classes, and that's it.",
      "word_count": 39
    }
  ],
